00:34:21.359 --> 00:34:36.398
Her life was better. Mine wasn't. I didn't get remarried. I was very angry—heavier than what I am now.

00:34:36.399 --> 00:34:47.279
He said, "I want to show you now: your son won't be born and there's a call on his life, and here in the future you'll have a little girl.

00:34:47.280 --> 00:35:08.239
You'll have a little girl, and she won't be born either, and she has a major call in her life too."He said, "Brandon..."He started preaching to me and he started talking to me about everything—to sum it up and not make this really long for y'all tonight because I'm already going over.

00:35:08.240 --> 00:35:37.039
But he said, "Brandon, I didn't cause Megan to have autism. I did not do this to you to teach you anything."He said to me, "The devil comes to kill, steal, and destroy.

00:35:37.040 --> 00:35:44.159
But what the devil meant for bad, I'll turn it around for good in your favor.

00:35:44.160 --> 00:35:50.739
You're not big enough to mess up your life. You're not big enough to mess up your life, Brandon.

00:35:50.740 --> 00:36:01.358
No matter how many bad choices you've made, he said, 'As long as the footsteps of the righteous are ordered of the Lord.

00:36:01.359 --> 00:36:09.118
And as long as you're right with me and you're seeking me, I'll turn it around.

00:36:09.119 --> 00:36:20.114
I'll turn what the devil meant for bad, Brandon, and I'll turn it around for good in your favor as long as you're looking towards me.'"Because in my mind, I always told him, "I can't do ministry.

00:36:20.115 --> 00:36:24.722
I can't lay hands on the sick. I can't do all that because of Megan, Lord.

00:36:24.723 --> 00:36:29.942
What do you call me to healing ministry? Well, you called me to do all these things.

00:36:29.943 --> 00:36:36.551
I'm broken because of this."But he said, "Brandon, Megan does not validate my word.

00:36:36.552 --> 00:36:46.348
My word validates itself. It's a pillar. Megan's healing doesn't validate that I'm a healer.

00:36:46.349 --> 00:37:05.999
My word validates that."As he said all these things to me, I saw the pressure from having a child with special needs.

00:37:06.000 --> 00:37:26.719
As I was ready to drive off a bridge, as I was ready to do away with myself so many different times, as I was driving home and crying behind the toilets, cleaning the church bathrooms, and doing all the things that I went through being a janitor for 15 years—it molded me.

00:37:26.720 --> 00:37:40.499
It took a really hard heart and made it soft as I had to buckle up and honor my wife and go through this very hard time raising a child with special needs.

00:37:40.500 --> 00:37:53.039
The pressure on the potter's wheel makes you different if you yield to it. It's the pressure.

00:37:53.040 --> 00:37:59.039
We have this treasure in earthen vessels that the excellency of the power will be known to him and not of us.

00:37:59.040 --> 00:38:15.358
But the pressure from Megan and all the things that I went through made me into who I am today.

00:38:15.359 --> 00:38:32.905
As he kept telling me that I couldn't mess my life up no matter how bad I've done things in the past, he said, "I told you if the footsteps of the righteous are ordered of the Lord."He encouraged me.

00:38:32.906 --> 00:38:39.999
He preached to me. He preached a really fiery message that I wish I could remember all of it.

00:38:40.000 --> 00:38:48.391
I've never heard Jesus as a preacher. And boy, he could preach fire. I'll never forget it.

00:38:48.392 --> 00:38:58.185
I sat there and watched him as he preached to me, and he told me that I had a call on my life and he wanted me to do something for him.

00:38:58.186 --> 00:39:07.639
I thought at that moment that I had totally derailed my life because of what the doctor had told us: that Megan would never be normal and that she would never be potty trained.

00:39:07.640 --> 00:39:15.679
She would never have a normal life, and we'd be lucky if she ever gets out of an 18-month-old's stage.

00:39:15.680 --> 00:39:22.356
But that's why I've tried to tell you all over and over again. Right now, we weren't able to do anything.

00:39:22.358 --> 00:39:29.165
If anybody realized how bad Megan was—she would urinate on everything. She would play with her feces every day.

00:39:29.166 --> 00:39:38.651
She would bite herself until blood would run down her hands, pull her hair out.

00:39:38.652 --> 00:39:51.645
She had huge bald spots all over her head where she'd pull all her hair out, take everything out of one drawer in one room and put it in there.

00:39:51.646 --> 00:39:58.956
I never knew where my toothbrush was. I never knew where my deodorant was. I never knew where my soap from my bathroom was.

00:39:58.957 --> 00:40:03.850
She'd take all the ornaments off the tree every single year and put them in the kitchen sink.

00:40:03.851 --> 00:40:16.959
We never could have a Christmas tree. We never could do anything. We did that for years. And then one day Jesus visited us.

00:40:16.960 --> 00:40:25.513
And in that time whenever he visited, I was at the sink and I was complaining, and I said to him, "You don't hear anything I'm saying?

00:40:25.514 --> 00:40:31.592
I prayed and prayed and prayed for her to get better."And I said, "She's not.

00:40:31.593 --> 00:40:38.639
Do you hear, and have you heard, any of my prayers?"I was washing the dishes.

00:40:38.640 --> 00:40:41.994
And at that time, the glory of the Lord filled my whole house.

00:40:41.995 --> 00:40:49.116
And I saw him visibly again. I was on the floor and Diana couldn't see him.

00:40:49.117 --> 00:40:56.959
I was on the floor and he melted me like wax. I thought I was going to die.

00:40:56.960 --> 00:41:03.919
The presence of the Lord was so strong in my house; I thought I was going to die.

00:41:03.920 --> 00:41:16.201
I looked up at him and I said, "Jesus, don't you know what I've asked for?"Because he asked me, the first thing he asked me was, "What do you have need of?"I said, "Don't you know what I have need of?

00:41:16.202 --> 00:41:26.639
Megan!"He said, "According to your faith, be it done unto you, Brandon.

00:41:26.640 --> 00:41:42.078
According to your faith, be it done unto you."Diana came around the corner at this time and she saw me on the floor and she felt the presence of the Lord so strong in the house and she thought I was dying.

00:41:42.079 --> 00:41:45.431
She started screaming. She says, "Jesus, don't take him. Don't take him.

00:41:45.432 --> 00:41:51.971
I need my husband. I can't do this on my own."She goes, "Is he dying? Are you dying?"And she started yelling.

00:41:51.972 --> 00:42:08.479
I said, "Jesus is here, honey."She says, "I know, I can feel it, but I can't see him."And I started crying out and he ministered to me and he put his hand on my head and he blessed me.

00:42:08.480 --> 00:42:23.679
He said, "She'll start to amend from this hour."And I knew it's going to be gradual like I've always told y'all; a miracle is a miracle even if it's not overnight.

00:42:23.680 --> 00:42:38.399
A miracle is a miracle even if it's progressive. I saw everything from that day forward—that I knew it was going to be a journey.

00:42:38.400 --> 00:42:48.274
But Jesus told me, "According to your faith, be it done unto you."When I woke up the next day, I went over and told my grandfather because we lived across the street at the time.

00:42:48.275 --> 00:42:55.439
I said, "Grandpa, we had a visitation from Jesus."Megan didn't act any different.

00:42:55.440 --> 00:43:07.234
I thought, "Surely if Jesus shows up in your house, Megan's going to be completely healed and it's going to be a sign and a wonder."Time goes by.

00:43:07.235 --> 00:43:23.051
This is a Friday, Saturday, Sunday, Monday—she goes to her little ABA therapy lady and she calls and she said, "Brandon, what happened to Megan?"I said, "Kimberly, what are you talking about?

00:43:23.052 --> 00:43:29.765
What happened to Megan?"She said, "Something's happened to Megan."I said, "What?

00:43:29.766 --> 00:43:40.318
What? Does she have a bruise? What is it?"Because you're thinking, "What are you accusing me of?"But it wasn't.

00:43:40.319 --> 00:43:47.039
She said, "She's saying little sentences. She's parroting something for the first time.

00:43:47.040 --> 00:43:55.292
Something's happened."She was saying red; she says blue. She says all these different colors that she was parroting from that day forward.

00:43:55.293 --> 00:44:03.919
And Megan still does those things. She even told me today, "Hi, daddy, mommy."She was talking to both of us.

00:44:03.920 --> 00:44:10.805
But from that time forward, it's been a step all the time and we keep seeing a little bit more.

00:44:10.806 --> 00:44:14.976
But then, even my family, nobody could even touch her hardly.

00:44:14.977 --> 00:44:20.225
She acted like she was a wild animal. It was absolutely hell on earth.

00:44:20.226 --> 00:44:25.163
But from that time forward when Jesus visited, she's gotten better and better.

00:44:25.164 --> 00:44:30.005
And it hasn't been instantaneous, like everything's better.

00:44:30.006 --> 00:44:33.899
Like the one with the issue of blood, I'm believing that moment's coming.

00:44:33.900 --> 00:44:39.679
But what I'm trying to tell you is that sometimes it's progressive.

00:44:39.680 --> 00:44:52.799
Now, between that and all that I've told you of two visitations tonight and just that short little bit of time, I cut them up in pieces to make that really quick for you.

00:44:52.800 --> 00:44:57.008
What I'm trying to tell you is I want you to believe God for it.

00:44:57.009 --> 00:45:12.063
No matter how bad you think you've disrupted your life and you think that you can't be used by God, and no matter how hard you think you've had it, the footsteps of the righteous are ordered by the Lord, and you're not big enough to derail your life.

00:45:12.064 --> 00:45:17.134
You can say, 'Well, Brandon, I was a prostitute. I was on drugs. I was in jail.

00:45:17.135 --> 00:45:21.645
I went and I did, I robbed banks.'Or maybe you're a wife beater.

00:45:21.646 --> 00:45:26.655
Maybe you were all these different things and your wife left you or whatever.

00:45:26.656 --> 00:45:41.999
But what I'm trying to tell you is that no matter how bad you think you are, no matter how bad you've disrupted your life, if you're seeking God, no matter how bad you've messed up, God will turn it on a dime.

00:45:42.000 --> 00:45:55.519
Never give up on what your dreams are. Never give up on what you're believing for. Always stay close to the vine.

00:45:55.520 --> 00:46:02.479
Regardless of how hard you think your life is, it's the pressure that changes you.

00:46:02.480 --> 00:46:10.369
You may have been a janitor. You may have been a store clerk. You may be somebody that was a gas attendant.

00:46:10.370 --> 00:46:20.078
It doesn't matter. Whatever you do, in word and in deed, do all to the glory of God.

00:46:20.079 --> 00:46:29.222
God will promote you in due time. It takes time sometimes because we have a lot of flesh in the way.

00:46:29.223 --> 00:46:34.956
In my circumstances, being a janitor for 15 years and having a child still right now that's overcoming...

00:46:34.957 --> 00:46:45.919
As we were driving home tonight, she was quiet. I said, 'Megan's okay. You want an ice cream?'So I went by and got her an ice cream.

00:46:45.920 --> 00:46:53.186
I thought about that a lot as we go through this Christmas season because I dread holidays a lot going around family.

00:46:53.187 --> 00:47:06.078
You think, 'Well, how is she going to act? How things are going?'But I can tell you Jesus has brought us so far even at Christmas time.

00:47:06.079 --> 00:47:12.754
So I don't know what you're going through tonight, but I try to just give you a little bit of encouragement to keep on keeping on.

00:47:12.755 --> 00:47:17.659
Don't be weary in well-doing. Don't be weary in well-doing in your job.

00:47:17.660 --> 00:47:25.919
And know that if you're on the potter's wheel, he always finishes a perfect product.

00:47:25.920 --> 00:47:35.039
There's no mistakes. There's no mistakes with the Father. You might be a rich billionaire.

00:47:35.040 --> 00:47:41.083
You might be watching this and you're worth hundreds of millions of dollars, but you're still a work in progress.

00:47:41.084 --> 00:47:51.858
No matter how much money you have, Jesus Christ loves you and he paid the price for you. He has a plan for your life.

00:47:51.859 --> 00:48:02.078
No matter how much depression you could be overcoming and everybody thinks you have it all together driving a Ferrari or whatever.

00:48:02.079 --> 00:48:09.936
I've noticed that there's a lot of people who have money that have it all that are the most depressed, saddest people with broken marriages more than anybody else.

00:48:09.938 --> 00:48:16.085
But I'm trying to tell you it's not about money. It's not about not having money.

00:48:16.086 --> 00:48:33.194
It's about seeking Jesus and having a relationship with him, and he'll turn your life around even whenever you feel like you're in the deepest, darkest hole if you just yield yourself over and say, 'Jesus, I need you.

00:48:33.195 --> 00:48:46.479
I can't do this on my own.'I'm so thankful that I yielded to the process of the potter's wheel.

00:48:46.480 --> 00:48:53.621
I'm not a finished work. I'm still on that potter's wheel every single day. I'm a work in progress. That's what we say all the time.

00:48:53.622 --> 00:48:59.969
But I can tell you this: my marriage is good, my kids are healthy, and they all love the Lord.

00:48:59.970 --> 00:49:08.719
I don't have everything perfect by no means. It's like you saw just at the beginning of this video, I was very angry.

00:49:08.720 --> 00:49:27.979
But it's the keep on keeping on that keeps you humble, keeps you ready, and keeps you willing and obedient to eat the good of the land. None of us have it all together. None of us do.

00:49:27.980 --> 00:49:51.103
No matter how much we try to pretend, it's like the highlight reel on Facebook or Instagram or whatever, and you see the fakeness of people and you look at it and go, 'I know what's going on behind closed doors.'You're like, 'We're pretending,'you know, 'selfie, Snapchat, hashtag everything's great.'And you look at them and go, 'Everything's great with you?

00:49:51.104 --> 00:50:03.439
You're faking it.'I see a lot of fakers. I think that's why I came over that inside of my heart. When you get real with God, God will become real to you.

00:50:03.440 --> 00:50:17.622
Because there's so many people that are faking it because they live the highlight reel of Facebook or X or whatever your platform is of your choice, Snapchat or whatever.

00:50:17.623 --> 00:50:27.618
I just want you to be real with God today. If you're here tonight and you're having a hard time during this holiday season and you're thinking, 'Man, I've derailed my life.

00:50:27.619 --> 00:50:36.959
I got a DUI. I got a DUI. And I'm driving home from this and I got pulled over and they took, they suspended my license.

00:50:36.960 --> 00:50:42.719
I've derailed my life.'The boss fired me. I couldn't make it to work.

00:50:42.720 --> 00:50:48.513
I don't know what I'm doing, but right now I'm at rock bottom and you just need prayer.

00:50:48.514 --> 00:50:59.313
Or you could be at the top of the mountain and you're looking down going, 'Man, I've got everything by the you-know-what, and I've got everything going and I've got more money in my bank account and I've got Rolexes.

00:50:59.314 --> 00:51:17.919
I've got all this stuff and I don't need anything from Jesus because I have it all.'What you don't have is joy in your soul. True joy. Riches without sorrow.

00:51:17.920 --> 00:51:27.519
No matter how much you think you can hoard it up on yourself and have it, riches without sorrow is joy unspeakable and full of glory.

00:51:27.520 --> 00:51:31.356
But it's appointed unto man once to die and after that judgment. That's the other part.

00:51:31.358 --> 00:51:39.598
You may think you have it all right now, but right now if you die, you're going to spend eternity in hell.

00:51:39.599 --> 00:51:48.856
'Well, I don't believe that, Brandon. I don't believe there's a hell.'Well, what if you're wrong? What if you're wrong?

00:51:48.857 --> 00:51:56.432
What if there is a hell and you took your whole life thinking that you had it all and you didn't need heaven?

00:51:56.433 --> 00:52:01.913
I don't believe there's a heaven or hell. I'm an agnostic. I'm an atheist.

00:52:01.914 --> 00:52:10.399
But I'm telling you, what if there is a hell? What if there is a heaven?

00:52:10.400 --> 00:52:25.434
Are you willing to take a gamble on an assumption? That's really foolish. I want to pray for you.

00:52:25.435 --> 00:52:30.680
There's 5,360 people here right now watching this and I want to pray for you.

00:52:30.681 --> 00:52:33.877
And you may be one of the people that I'm talking to and you've derailed your life.

00:52:33.878 --> 00:52:43.199
You think you've messed up everything, but you just wanted some encouragement tonight from somebody who has messed up a lot.

00:52:43.200 --> 00:52:48.372
And I'm telling you, I'm a work in progress, but I see fruit in my life that God has been with me.

00:52:48.373 --> 00:52:54.926
He's an ever-present help in a time of need. But he'll do the same for you because he's no respecter of persons.

00:52:54.927 --> 00:53:03.679
Brandon's not special. My wife's not special. She's special to me. She's special to Jesus.

00:53:03.680 --> 00:53:14.558
But I want to tell you that the same Jesus that set us free will set you free. And I want to pray for you right now.

00:53:14.559 --> 00:53:31.598
And if you're here tonight and you're backslidden and you're on your way to hell, if you've never asked Jesus Christ to be your Lord and personal savior and you're here tonight and you're frustrated with the holiday season, you're frustrated with your family, you don't really want to go around them, you've got all these issues going on in your life, but you just need a friend.

00:53:31.599 --> 00:53:45.039
If you just need some peace in your heart to sleep at night, I want to pray for you. I believe it's not coincidence that you're here tonight.

00:53:45.040 --> 00:53:54.944
You might be a person that never wants to watch this kind of stuff, but you just so happen to click this video and you're like, 'What is going on with this channel?

00:53:54.945 --> 00:54:07.598
Why is there so many people watching this guy in the middle of the night?'But I just want to pray for you right now and I want you to get real with God tonight.

00:54:07.599 --> 00:54:16.009
If you're here tonight and you want to ask Jesus Christ to be your Lord personal savior, I want you to put in the comment section right now below, 'I need to be saved.

00:54:16.010 --> 00:54:22.311
I want to be saved. I want to be a Christian. I want to make a change in my life right now.

00:54:22.312 --> 00:54:50.399
I don't want to keep going down this life; I don't want to keep doing this without him.'If you're here tonight and that's you, and I'm talking to you and you feel that itching on the inside of you—your stomach might have butterflies, you might be having cold sweats right now, and you're going, 'Man, I feel like he's talking to me.'I am talking to you.

00:54:50.400 --> 00:54:55.679
But tonight's your night; you may not have another opportunity.

00:54:55.680 --> 00:55:00.385
There's so many times I see a vision; I see these things the Lord shows me.

00:55:00.386 --> 00:55:11.598
