00:55:11.599 --> 00:55:20.292
It was so accurate, even to the number that got shot in LA, and the Lord told us it was coming.

00:55:20.293 --> 00:55:36.399
But I wished I could have gone there and told those people at that birthday party, 'Please, you must know Jesus Christ as your Lord and personal savior.'I hope they knew him.

00:55:36.400 --> 00:55:43.570
I hope they were given the opportunity, like you're being given the opportunity right now, to accept Jesus Christ.

00:55:43.572 --> 00:56:02.399
No one knows the day they will die. The very shoes you put on today to go to work, the undertaker might be taking them off that evening. No one knows; no one is promised tomorrow.

00:56:02.400 --> 00:56:13.598
But if you're here tonight and you just want to make a clean start for 2026—we're almost there—why keep living in the hell you're living in?

00:56:13.599 --> 00:56:23.679
Change now. Make a change. To do the same thing over and over again and expect different results is what?

00:56:23.680 --> 00:56:32.159
Insanity. So I'm giving you an opportunity tonight. Make a change. I'm going to say a simple prayer.

00:56:32.160 --> 00:56:36.959
It's simple; a five-year-old can say it, mean it, and believe it, and have change.

00:56:36.960 --> 00:56:47.503
It doesn't have to be all religious. I hate religion. I'm going to tell you that I'm the most unreligious person that you'll ever meet.

00:56:47.504 --> 00:56:53.199
Ask my family; Brandon is not religious. I'm about relationship.

00:56:53.200 --> 00:57:03.759
So, I'm going to say a prayer for you and I want you to say it back with me, and I want you to mean it with your whole heart because the Bible says with the heart confession is made unto salvation.

00:57:03.760 --> 00:57:10.759
